>
    <main>
        <section class="page-header">
                    <div class="orb orb-1"></div>
                    <div class="orb orb-2"></div>
                    <h1>About <span class="gradient-text">Commerce AI</span></h1>
                    <p>Accelerating the adoption of AI-powered commerce through open standards</p>
                </section>

                <div class="page-body">
                    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
                    <p>Commerce AI was created with a singular mission: <strong>to help every online store become ready for the age of AI-powered commerce</strong>. As artificial intelligence transforms how consumers shop — with AI agents autonomously discovering, comparing, and purchasing products — we believe every merchant deserves free, accessible tools to participate in this revolution.</p>
                    <p>Our flagship product, the <strong>UCP Compliance Checker</strong>, is the first and most comprehensive tool for validating compliance with Google's Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP). We built it because we saw a gap: an emerging standard with enormous potential, but no easy way for store owners to check if they're ready.</p>

                    <h2>What We Do</h2>
                    <p>We build free, developer-friendly tools that bridge the gap between traditional e-commerce and the emerging world of agentic commerce. Our UCP Compliance Checker performs <strong>15 automated checks</strong> on your store's UCP profile, providing instant feedback with actionable remediation steps.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Profile Validation:</strong> We verify that your <code>/.well-known/ucp</code> endpoint exists and returns properly structured JSON.</li>
                        <li><strong>Security Auditing:</strong> We ensure all your endpoints use HTTPS and your store follows security best practices.</li>
                        <li><strong>Structure Analysis:</strong> We check that your services, capabilities, and naming conventions conform to the UCP specification.</li>
                        <li><strong>Scoring & Reporting:</strong> We provide a weighted compliance score with severity-graded results so you know exactly what to fix first.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>Why UCP Matters</h2>
                    <p>The Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP) is an open standard developed by Google that enables AI agents — like Google Gemini — to interface directly with online stores. Instead of browsing websites like humans do, AI agents read machine-readable UCP profiles to understand what a store offers and how to interact with it.</p>
                    <p>This isn't a future possibility — it's happening now. Google has already begun integrating UCP into its AI ecosystem. Stores that adopt the standard early will capture a growing share of AI-mediated purchases, while those that don't risk becoming invisible to an entirely new channel of commerce.</p>

                    <h2>Our Values</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Free & Open:</strong> Our tools are free to use, no account required. We believe accessibility drives adoption.</li>
                        <li><strong>Privacy-First:</strong> We don't store the URLs you scan or the results. Every check is stateless and ephemeral.</li>
                        <li><strong>Community-Driven:</strong> We follow and contribute to the open UCP specification, ensuring our tools stay aligned with the latest standards.</li>
                        <li><strong>Developer-Friendly:</strong> We build tools that developers love — fast, accurate, and with clear, actionable output.</li>
                    </ul>

